(59, 'AMG2405', 'AUGMENTED & VIRTUAL REALITY', 3, 2, 2, 0, 25, 0, 5, 30, 70, 'Students will be able to develop interactive AR/VR applications using Unity and other development tools.\nStudents will be able to apply user experience design principles to create effective AR/VR applications.\nStudents will be able to use 3D modeling and animation techniques to create engaging AR/VR environments and characters.\nStudents will be able to develop multiplayer AR/VR applications and applications for mobile devices', 'To provide students with a comprehensive understanding of AR/VR technology and its applications in various industries.\nTo teach students how to use Unity and other AR/VR development tools to create interactive applications.\nTo develop students creative problem-solving, critical thinking, and teamwork skills through the design and execution of AR/VR projects.\nTo prepare students for careers in AR/VR development, game design, and related fields', 'Overview of AR/VR technology and its applications.\nIntroduction to Unity and other AR/VR development tools.\nBasic programming concepts for AR/VR. ', 10, 'AR/VR Design and Development\nUser experience design for AR/VR\nDeveloping interactive AR/VR applications\nIntroduction to 3D modeling and animation for AR/VR', 10, 'Advanced AR/VR Development\nAdvanced programming concepts for AR/VR\nDeveloping multiplayer AR/VR applications\nDeveloping AR/VR applications for mobile devices', 10, 'Final Project\nStudents will work in teams to develop a final AR/VR\nproject using the skills and techniques they\'ve learned throughout the course\nEmphasis on creative problem-solving, effective communication, and collaboration', 15, 'NA', 0, 'Books on Google Play\nVirtual and Augmented Reality (VR/AR): Foundations and Methods of Extended Realities (XR)'),
(60, 'AMG2406', 'MOTION GRAPHICS', 3, 2, 2, 0, 25, 10, 5, 30, 70, 'NEED TO CREATE', 'NEED TO CREATE', 'NEED TO CREATE', 0, 'NEED TO CREATE', 0, 'NEED TO CREATE', 0, 'NEED TO CREATE', 0, 'NEED TO CREATE', 0, 'NEED TO CREATE'),
(61, 'AMG2507', 'WEB & E-BUSINESS', 3, 2, 2, 0, 25, 0, 5, 30, 70, 'Understand the fundamentals of web development and design, including HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.\nDevelop front-end and back-end components of a gaming website or online platform.\nApply user experience design principles to create intuitive and engaging interfaces for gaming websites.\nImplement e-business strategies specific to the gaming industry, including monetization models and marketing techniques.', 'Gain a comprehensive understanding of web development technologies and their application in the gaming industry.\nDevelop practical skills in HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and other relevant web development languages and frameworks.\nApply user-centered design principles to create intuitive and visually appealing interfaces for gaming websites.\nExplore various e-business models and strategies specific to the gaming industry.', 'Module I: Introduction to Web & E-Business\nOverview of web technologies\nHTML basics and structure\nCSS fundamentals for web design\n', 12, 'Module II: Front-End Development\nIntroduction to JavaScript\nManipulating the Document Object Model (DOM)\nManipulating the Document Object Model (DOM)', 8, 'Module III: Back-End Development\nIntroduction to server-side programming\nIntroduction to databases and SQL\nIntegrating front-end and back-end technologies\nPrinciples of user-centered design\nWireframing and prototyping\nUsability testing and optimization\nIntroduction to e-business models', 15, 'Module IV: E-Commerce Platforms \nOverview of e-commerce platforms\nOverview of e-commerce platforms\nPayment gateways and security considerations\nBasics of SEO and its importance\nOn-page and off-page optimization for gaming websites\nSEO tools and analytics\nSocial media marketing for gaming', 10, 'NA', 0, '\"Web Design with HTML, CSS, JavaScript and jQuery Set\" by Jon Duckett\nThis book provides a comprehensive introduction to web design and development, covering HTML,\nCSS, JavaScript, and jQuery. It offers clear explanations and practical examples that can be applied\nto gaming websites.\n\"Don\'t Make Me Think, Revisited: A Common Sense Approach to Web Usability\" by Steve Krug\nThis book focuses on user experience design and usability principles. It provides valuable insights\ninto creating intuitive and user-friendly interfaces, which is crucial for designing engaging gaming\nwebsites.'),
(62, 'AMG2503', 'GAME SPECIAL EFFECTS', 3, 2, 2, 0, 25, 0, 5, 30, 70, 'Understand the importance and impact of special effects in video games.\nFamiliarity with industry-standard tools and software for creating game special effects.\nAbility to design and implement particle systems for various effects.\nProficiency in creating and manipulating shaders for visual effects', 'Understand the significance of special effects in video games.\nGain proficiency in industry-standard tools for game special effects.\nLearn to design and implement particle systems for various effects.\nDevelop skills in shader programming for creating visually appealing effects', 'Module I: Introduction to Game Special Effects\nOverview of special effects in video games\nImportance and impact of special effects on gameplay\nIntroduction to industry-standard tools and software', 12, 'Module II: Understanding Particle Systems\nBasics of particle systems\nCreating and manipulating particles\nParticle simulation and behavior', 8, 'Module III: Shader Fundamentals\nShader programming languages (e.g., HLSL, GLSL)\nImplementing basic shaders for visual effects\nShader-based effects such as distortion, refraction,and reflection\nCreating complex materials and textures\nProcedural shader generation\nImplementing depth of field, motion blur, and bloom effects', 15, 'Module IV: Post-Processing Effects\nIntroduction to post-processing and image effects\nColor grading and visual enhancement techniques\nDesigning effects for stylized games\nImplementing cel shading, toon effects, and other artistic styles\nTechniques for conveying emotions through effects\nScripting and integration techniques\nPerformance optimization for real-time effects', 10, 'NA', 0, '\"Real-Time Rendering\" by Tomas Akenine-Möller, Eric Haines, and Naty Hoffman\n\"GPU Gems\" series by various authors\n\"Game Engine Architecture\" by Jason Gregory\n\"Unity in Action: Multiplatform Game Development in C#\" by Joe Hocking'),
